trans-unit.source: Defines the interface for an STL/CLR [list](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/a70c45c8-a257-4f6b-8434-b27ff6685bac) object.
The type of a list element.
Replaces the controlled sequence with the sequence that is designated by the given enumerator.
For more information, see [list::assign (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/c5f2b131-d0e1-4188-9d4b-d617280e4032).
The enumeration whose elements are to be inserted into the container.
Replaces the controlled sequence with the sequence [_First,_Last).
For more information, see [list::assign (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/c5f2b131-d0e1-4188-9d4b-d617280e4032).
The beginning position of the range of elements to insert into the container.
The first position beyond the range of elements to insert into the container.
Replaces the controlled sequence with the specified number of the given element.
For more information, see [list::assign (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/c5f2b131-d0e1-4188-9d4b-d617280e4032).
The number of elements to insert into the container.
The value of the elements to insert into the container.
Accesses the last element of the container.
For more information, see [list::back (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/3241e497-42ab-4108-8598-3f90eac76f07).
The last element of the controlled sequence, which must be non-empty.
Accesses the last element of the container.
For more information, see [list::back_item (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/63dcdd21-61f7-4e0f-88a7-c9c8f8a2c50a).
The last element of the controlled sequence, which must be non-empty.
Designates the beginning of the controlled sequence.
For more information, see [list::begin (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/3431467b-951a-498a-af8d-50f631da1646).
An iterator.
Removes all elements from the container.
For more information, see [list::clear (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/5aac9a64-52f6-4a73-8b24-e30ceedcbc20).
Tests whether the container has no elements.
For more information, see [list::empty (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/f45edf8a-927d-41ff-9c09-cb0fba4f08b8).
`true` if the container has no elements; otherwise, `false`.
Designates the end of the controlled sequence.
For more information, see [list::end (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/c3444164-2c6e-4cbd-8765-1ce7d30fc43e).
An iterator.
Accesses the first element of the container.
For more information, see [list::front (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ead6aaaa-b518-4a9c-af80-7189bf872cad).
The first element of the controlled sequence, which must be non-empty.
Accesses the first element of the container.
For more information, see [list::front_item (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/c871873b-7745-442b-9760-9d8096fa8610).
The first element of the controlled sequence, which must be non-empty.
Merges two ordered controlled sequences.
For more information, see [list::merge (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/f8e93cd3-bd08-4086-859b-08a2899cc9a6).
The container to merge into this container.
The Boolean functor for comparing pairs of elements.
Removes the last element from the container.
For more information, see [list::pop_back (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/03fe8e0e-461b-41c4-8e20-97d0d4ed0feb).
Removes the first element from the container.
For more information, see [list::pop_front (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/6a0bad42-6796-41d9-a3e9-1488b3882574).
Adds a new element to the end of the container.
For more information, see [list::push_back (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/f2c70470-a899-4e5f-8f3e-b55d6a8bff0e).
The value of the element to append to the container.
Adds a new element to the beginning of the container.
For more information, see [list::push_front (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/47525641-1139-44fc-ac62-bdc04876d9e0).
The value of the element to insert at the beginning of the container.
Designates the beginning of the reversed controlled sequence.
For more information, see [list::rbegin (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/99637376-8ac3-4e39-844a-b4f324a7c6ba).
An iterator.
Removes an element that has a specified value from the container.
For more information, see [list::remove (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/eaf598ee-e8fd-4cc0-be69-ca81a80e1d51).
The value of the element to remove from the container.
Designates the end of the reversed controlled sequence.
For more information, see [list::rend (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/b51030ad-1bca-42b0-b890-db47111d2921).
An iterator.
Changes the number of elements in the container to the specified size.
If the new size is larger than the old size, the given values will be appended to the container.
For more information, see [list::resize (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/c4b8d41f-a62b-4dbc-8568-0e0a9da24016).
The new size of the container.
The value of the padding elements.
Changes the number of elements in the container to the specified size.
For more information, see [list::resize (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/c4b8d41f-a62b-4dbc-8568-0e0a9da24016).
The new size of the container.
Reverses the elements of the controlled sequence.
For more information, see [list::reverse (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/de3bce1e-01fe-461d-a785-5cf4fcea988f).
Counts the number of elements in the container.
For more information, see [list::size (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/409e39fb-4468-44bb-b179-52c90e2fa293).
The length of the controlled sequence.
Orders the controlled sequence.
For more information, see [list::sort (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/f811d5f4-a19e-4194-8765-1e68097c52f0).
The operator that will be used to compare elements for ordering.
Swaps the contents of two containers.
For more information, see [list::swap (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/188b66c2-0a08-4001-a566-41d0955c89bd).
The container to swap contents with.
Removes adjacent elements that pass a specified test.
For more information, see [list::unique (STL/CLR)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/c3a29e4e-0ec1-4472-b050-7a9511037132).
The comparer that determines whether element pairs are unique.
An element that is not unique will be removed from the container.
